708
00:44:26,347 --> 00:44:28,425
HOW MANY CALLS DID WE
MAKE ON THIS PHONE, ALAN?

709
00:44:28,449 --> 00:44:29,515
12, MAMAW.

710
00:44:29,584 --> 00:44:30,883
12.

711
00:44:30,952 --> 00:44:32,685
AND AS THE SUN

712
00:44:32,754 --> 00:44:36,756
WENT FROM A FRIENDLY-
MORNING SMILEY FACE OVER THERE

713
00:44:36,824 --> 00:44:39,725
TO A HOT, ANGRY BLAZE UP THERE,

714
00:44:39,794 --> 00:44:43,128
WE DISCUSSED THE SUMMER WEATHER

715
00:44:43,998 --> 00:44:45,798
AND BEING HERE IN IT

716
00:44:45,867 --> 00:44:50,069
WITH NEITHER A HOUSE
KEY NOR A DADDY IN SIGHT.

717
00:44:50,137 --> 00:44:52,315
[Mrs. Barlow] WHAT
ELSE DID WE DISCUSS?

718
00:44:52,339 --> 00:44:53,973
BIKES, MAMAW.

719
00:44:54,042 --> 00:44:55,252
BIKES.

720
00:44:55,276 --> 00:44:59,045
WE SAW A BICYCLE
RACE, RIGHT OUT HERE.

721
00:44:59,113 --> 00:45:01,480
AND WE COUNTED
THEM AS THEY WENT BY.

722
00:45:01,549 --> 00:45:03,594
ONE OF THE GROUPS OF CYCLISTS

723
00:45:03,618 --> 00:45:07,519
WAS SO LARGE, WE LOST COUNT.

724
00:45:07,589 --> 00:45:12,058
AND WE WONDERED, WHAT DO
YOU CALL A GROUP OF CYCLISTS?

725
00:45:12,894 --> 00:45:14,705
A... A CLUSTER?

726
00:45:14,729 --> 00:45:16,428
A HERD?

727
00:45:16,497 --> 00:45:17,763
A GAGGLE.

728
00:45:18,566 --> 00:45:19,832
PELOTON.

729
00:45:19,901 --> 00:45:24,203
A PELOTON OF CYCLISTS.

730
00:45:24,271 --> 00:45:26,216
YOU KNOW A WORD LIKE THAT,

731
00:45:26,240 --> 00:45:29,041
AND YOU DON'T KNOW
THE MEANING OF "MORNING."

732
00:45:29,110 --> 00:45:30,743
I'VE BEEN PRETTY BUSY.

733
00:45:30,812 --> 00:45:34,513
AND I HAVE ABSOLUTELY
NOTHING TO DO, GETTING THEM FED,

734
00:45:34,582 --> 00:45:36,863
MAKING AN EMERGENCY
RUN TO THE DRUGSTORE.

735
00:45:36,918 --> 00:45:37,918
EMERGENCY RUN?

736
00:45:37,952 --> 00:45:39,029
NEVER MIND.

737
00:45:39,053 --> 00:45:40,965
HOT, BLAZING SUN HALF THE DAY.

738
00:45:40,989 --> 00:45:42,421
I SAID I WAS SORRY.

739
00:45:42,490 --> 00:45:44,090
NO, YOU DIDN'T.

740
00:45:45,927 --> 00:45:47,593
NOT A WHIFF OF IT.

741
00:45:50,632 --> 00:45:53,232
I'M SORRY. I'M SORRY. I'M SORRY.

742
00:46:05,579 --> 00:46:07,860
I'M SORRY. I'M SORRY.
I'M SORRY I'M LATE.

743
00:46:09,667 --> 00:46:11,462
[Marilyn] <i>THE POINT
IS THAT YOUR MOTHER</i>

744
00:46:11,486 --> 00:46:13,264
<i>BROUGHT THE KIDS TO YOUR HOUSE</i>

745
00:46:13,288 --> 00:46:15,721
<i>AND SHE HAD TO
CANCEL HER ENTIRE DAY</i>

746
00:46:15,790 --> 00:46:17,434
<i>WHILE YOU WERE, I DON'T KNOW,</i>

747
00:46:17,458 --> 00:46:20,459
<i>CRAWLING OUT OF SOME
DITCH SOMEWHERE, NO DOUBT?</i>

748
00:46:22,630 --> 00:46:25,665
<i>SO WHY ARE YOU CALLING ME? HMM?</i>

749
00:46:25,733 --> 00:46:28,033
<i>DO YOU KNOW THAT
THIS IS THE FIRST NIGHT</i>

750
00:46:28,102 --> 00:46:31,136
<i>THAT I'VE HAD TO
MYSELF IN 2 WEEKS?</i>

751
00:46:31,205 --> 00:46:33,539
<i>HERE YOU ARE, CHATTING ME UP.</i>

752
00:46:34,542 --> 00:46:36,208
YOU IN THE BATHTUB?

753
00:46:37,011 --> 00:46:38,011
NO.

754
00:46:42,317 --> 00:46:43,317
NO.

755
00:46:44,719 --> 00:46:47,953
THAT'S JUST THE SOUND
OF YOU PISSING UP A ROPE.

756
00:46:48,022 --> 00:46:49,154
[Giggles]

757
00:46:52,393 --> 00:46:54,360
WHY DON'T YOU COME OVER?

758
00:47:05,072 --> 00:47:06,305
MARILYN?

759
00:47:12,714 --> 00:47:13,879
MARILYN?

760
00:47:16,083 --> 00:47:17,516
[Sobbing]

761
00:47:30,965 --> 00:47:31,864
MONROE.

762
00:47:31,932 --> 00:47:32,998
♪ [Jazz music playing]

763
00:47:33,067 --> 00:47:35,100
THAT'S ME AND MONROE.

764
00:47:36,303 --> 00:47:37,970
THAT'S ME AND MONROE.

765
00:47:44,979 --> 00:47:46,846
I'VE GOT TO MEET MONROE.

