<i>♪ ALL OF THEM NIGHTS ♪</i>

1373
01:28:34,426 --> 01:28:39,062
<i>♪ DOWN IN MEXICO ♪</i>

1374
01:28:39,131 --> 01:28:43,033
<i>♪ THAT'S ONE PLACE
I'LL NEVER GO ♪</i>

1375
01:28:44,937 --> 01:28:48,305
<i>♪ IN MY LIFE AGAIN ♪</i>

1376
01:28:51,977 --> 01:28:53,944
<i>♪ OH, WAS I ♪</i>

1377
01:28:54,880 --> 01:28:57,380
<i>♪ OFF SOMEWHERE ♪</i>

1378
01:28:57,449 --> 01:29:00,783
<i>♪ OR MAYBE JUST TOO HIGH ♪</i>

1379
01:29:04,857 --> 01:29:06,456
<i>♪ BUT I ♪</i>

1380
01:29:06,524 --> 01:29:09,392
<i>♪ CAN'T REMEMBER ♪</i>

1381
01:29:09,461 --> 01:29:13,163
<i>♪ IF WE SAID GOODBYE ♪</i>

1382
01:29:17,035 --> 01:29:18,501
<i>♪ BUT I ♪</i>

1383
01:29:18,570 --> 01:29:21,504
<i>♪ CAN'T REMEMBER ♪</i>

1384
01:29:21,573 --> 01:29:24,707
<i>♪ IF WE SAID GOODBYE ♪</i>

1385
01:29:26,611 --> 01:29:28,011
<i>♪ GOODBYE ♪</i>

1386
01:29:29,314 --> 01:29:31,348
<i>♪ GOODBYE ♪</i>

1387
01:29:33,518 --> 01:29:35,118
[Birds sing]

1388
01:30:25,570 --> 01:30:27,115
[DeLoreo] <i>"BRAVO, LEON BARLOW.</i>

1389
01:30:27,139 --> 01:30:29,605
"BACKWARDS WEDDING
<i>KNOCKED US ALL OUT.</i>

1390
01:30:29,674 --> 01:30:32,175
<i>"HOW'S IT FEEL NOT
GETTING THE STORY BACK?</i>

1391
01:30:32,244 --> 01:30:34,777
<i>"WINTER ISSUE, FRONT AND CENTER.</i>

1392
01:30:34,846 --> 01:30:37,880
<i>"NEED A BIO TO PRINT, SOCIAL
SECURITY NUMBER TO PAY.</i>

1393
01:30:37,950 --> 01:30:42,218
<i>"SEND THOSE A.S.A.P. BUT YOU
NOW HAVE BIGGER FISH TO FRY.</i>

1394
01:30:42,287 --> 01:30:43,697
<i>"THAT NEW YORK FRIEND OF MINE</i>

1395
01:30:43,721 --> 01:30:45,366
<i>"WANTS TO SEE THE
REST OF THE BOOK.</i>

1396
01:30:45,390 --> 01:30:46,801
<i>"IF IT'S ALL GENUINE BARLOW,</i>

1397
01:30:46,825 --> 01:30:49,170
<i>"YOU'RE OUT OF THE SLUSH
PILE. ARE YOU READY?"</i>

1398
01:30:49,194 --> 01:30:50,226
AM I READY?

1399
01:30:50,295 --> 01:30:52,295
<i>"CHEERS. BETTI D."</i>

1400
01:30:59,938 --> 01:31:02,238
♪ [Tom Waits singing
<i>Long Way Home]</i>

1401
01:31:02,307 --> 01:31:06,309
<i>♪ WELL, I STUMBLED
IN THE DARKNESS ♪</i>

1402
01:31:06,378 --> 01:31:09,179
<i>♪ LOST AND ALONE ♪</i>

1403
01:31:10,315 --> 01:31:13,883
<i>♪ THOUGH I SEEN HER GO BEFORE ♪</i>

1404
01:31:14,886 --> 01:31:18,288
<i>♪ SHOW THE WAY BACK HOME ♪</i>

1405
01:31:19,491 --> 01:31:23,659
<i>♪ IS THERE A LIGHT UP AHEAD? ♪</i>

1406
01:31:23,728 --> 01:31:26,796
<i>♪ CAN'T HOLD ON VERY LONG ♪</i>

1407
01:31:28,166 --> 01:31:30,166
<i>♪ FORGIVE ME, PRETTY BABY ♪</i>

1408
01:31:30,235 --> 01:31:32,802
<i>♪ BUT I ALWAYS TAKE
THE LONG WAY HOME ♪</i>

1409
01:31:38,977 --> 01:31:40,877
IT'S SOMETHING, AIN'T IT?

1410
01:31:42,381 --> 01:31:44,214
GET IN, I'LL TELL
YOU ALL ABOUT IT.

1411
01:31:45,884 --> 01:31:47,450
HE'S REALLY OUT OF IT.

1412
01:32:00,132 --> 01:32:03,833
YOU KNOW HOW HARD IT IS TO REPLACE
SOMETHING SO OLD AND BEAT-UP?

1413
01:32:03,902 --> 01:32:05,768
YOU WOULD NOT BELIEVE.

1414
01:32:07,139 --> 01:32:09,039
A FEW DETAILS ARE OFF, BUT,

1415
01:32:09,107 --> 01:32:11,252
IT'S CLOSE ENOUGH TO THE
ORIGINAL TO BE A MINOR MIRACLE.

1416
01:32:11,276 --> 01:32:12,556
ISN'T IT, HONEY BOY?

1417
01:32:13,878 --> 01:32:16,946
HE WAS SO HYPER
ABOUT GOING FOR A DRIVE.

1418
01:32:17,015 --> 01:32:19,015
I HAD TO GIVE HIM AN EXTRA DOSE.

1419
01:32:19,084 --> 01:32:20,683
I MIGHT'VE OVERDONE IT.

1420
01:32:24,222 --> 01:32:26,622
OH, HEY, MY CAR'S BACK THAT WAY.

1421
01:32:29,294 --> 01:32:30,660
SLIDE OVER.

1422
01:32:35,833 --> 01:32:38,201
WHY DON'T YOU TAKE
ME WHERE I TELL YOU?

1423
01:32:40,738 --> 01:32:42,683
[Velma] TRY GETTING
US THERE IN ONE PIECE.

1424
01:32:42,707 --> 01:32:44,006
[Velma chuckling]

1425
01:32:47,179 --> 01:32:48,545
[Pig squeals]

1426
01:32:56,721 --> 01:32:59,755
I THOUGHT WE'D TAKE A DRIVE OUT TO
THE BOULEVARD OF BROKEN HUMAN HEADS.

1427
01:33:02,060 --> 01:33:04,327
YOU REMEMBER THE FIRST
TIME WE COME OUT HERE?

1428
01:33:06,831 --> 01:33:08,864
NO.

1429
01:33:08,933 --> 01:33:12,569
I SWEAR, NOTHING'S REAL TO
YOU, EXCEPT WHAT'S IN YOUR HEAD.

1430
01:33:18,477 --> 01:33:20,009
YOU GET RAPED IN JAIL?

1431
01:33:22,847 --> 01:33:26,149
MET A COUPLE OF NICE GUYS,
IT NEVER WENT ANYWHERE.

1432
01:33:26,218 --> 01:33:28,151
[Laughs]

1433
01:33:28,220 --> 01:33:30,820
GUESS IT'S NOT
EXACTLY STATE PEN.

1434
01:33:33,758 --> 01:33:35,125
BUT YOU KNOW,

1435
01:33:36,060 --> 01:33:37,693
YOU EVER NOTICE HOW,

1436
01:33:39,431 --> 01:33:41,131
YOU KNOW, THERE HE IS?

1437
01:33:43,668 --> 01:33:47,937
YOU EVER HAVE A JOB HE DIDN'T GET
FOR YOU OR WORK RIGHT ALONGSIDE YOU?

1438
01:33:49,073 --> 01:33:52,041
EVEN PULPWOOD AND LUMBERJACKING.

1439
01:33:52,110 --> 01:33:55,077
BET YOU NEVER KNEW
HOW MUCH HE HATED THAT.

1440
01:33:55,147 --> 01:33:57,880
IF YOU'D HAVE JUST LET
HIM GIVE YOU A MILLION OR 2,

1441
01:33:57,949 --> 01:34:01,584
NEITHER ONE OF YOU WOULD
HAVE HAD TO WORK SO HARD.

1442
01:34:01,653 --> 01:34:05,755
COURSE NOW, HE MIGHT NOT
EVEN REMEMBER HE'S RICH.

1443
01:34:05,823 --> 01:34:08,324
YOU KNOW, HE'S MISSING
WHOLE CHUNKS OF HIS LIFE.

1444
01:34:11,029 --> 01:34:13,596
I KNOW HE REMEMBERS
THE WAR, 'CAUSE I QUIZ HIM.

1445
01:34:15,367 --> 01:34:17,800
BUT, YOU KNOW, HE MIGHT NOT
REMEMBER OWING HIS LIFE TO YOU.

1446
01:34:17,869 --> 01:34:19,935
NO. NO.

1447
01:34:20,004 --> 01:34:21,504
HE SAVED MY LIFE.

1448
01:34:22,707 --> 01:34:24,840
HALF OF ONE, 6 A
DOZEN THE OTHER.

1449
01:34:37,822 --> 01:34:40,356
I DON'T THINK HE'S
EVER COMING BACK.

1450
01:34:42,060 --> 01:34:44,160
I MEAN...

1451
01:34:44,229 --> 01:34:45,806
HE'LL PROBABLY BE
BETTER THAN HE IS NOW,

1452
01:34:45,830 --> 01:34:48,565
BUT IF HE WAS COMING
ALL THE WAY BACK,

1453
01:34:48,633 --> 01:34:50,933
HE'D BE WAY FARTHER
ALONG BY NOW.

1454
01:34:54,606 --> 01:34:57,907
IT'S ONLY PEOPLE WHO KNEW HIM
BEFORE WILL REMEMBER THAT HE...

1455
01:34:58,943 --> 01:35:00,776
WASN'T ALWAYS LIKE THIS.

1456
01:35:03,014 --> 01:35:04,681
THEN AFTER A WHILE,

1457
01:35:06,017 --> 01:35:07,650
WE WON'T REMEMBER EITHER.

1458
01:35:10,938 --> 01:35:11,938
IF...

1459
01:35:13,692 --> 01:35:15,858
OK, OK, HERE'S THE THING.

1460
01:35:17,762 --> 01:35:20,129
I... I CAN'T ASK NOBODY ELSE.

1461
01:35:20,198 --> 01:35:21,664
IT'S GOT TO BE YOU.

1462
01:35:23,401 --> 01:35:25,000
WHAT I REALLY WANT

1463
01:35:26,204 --> 01:35:30,607
IS FOR THE KIND OF MAN
HE WAS TO BE KNOWN.

1464
01:35:30,675 --> 01:35:33,776
WILL YOU TELL THE
STORIES? WRITE SOME THINGS,

1465
01:35:33,845 --> 01:35:35,578
SO THAT WE DON'T EVER FORGET.

1466
01:35:36,948 --> 01:35:38,013
[Crying]

1467
01:35:42,019 --> 01:35:43,859
[Leon] <i>FRIENDLY PERSUASION.</i>

1468
01:35:44,656 --> 01:35:46,456
<i>WE SAW HALF THE SHOW.</i>

1469
01:35:48,526 --> 01:35:51,327
[Velma] <i>IT EVENTUALLY ALL
COMES BACK TO YOU, DOESN'T IT?</i>

1470
01:35:52,897 --> 01:35:56,599
<i>♪ WATER'S JUST SOAKING THROUGH ♪</i>

1471
01:35:56,668 --> 01:36:01,170
<i>♪ OFF THE BACK OF A TRAIN ♪</i>

1472
01:36:01,239 --> 01:36:04,774
<i>♪ THOUGHT WE'RE
HEADED FOR LIGHTENING ♪</i>

1473
01:36:05,744 --> 01:36:08,978
<i>♪ HAT FULL OF RAIN ♪</i>

1474
01:36:10,282 --> 01:36:14,417
<i>♪ AND I KNOW THAT I SAID ♪</i>

1475
01:36:14,486 --> 01:36:17,420
<i>♪ I'D NEVER DO IT AGAIN ♪</i>

1476
01:36:19,624 --> 01:36:24,727
<i>♪ I LOVE YOU, PRETTY BABY, BUT I
ALWAYS TAKE THE LONG WAY HOME ♪</i>

1477
01:36:29,417 --> 01:36:32,435
[Marilyn] YOU'D BETTER GET
UP HERE BEFORE YOU SINK.

1478
01:36:48,720 --> 01:36:51,321
GOD, THIS IS HOW BEAT I AM.

1479
01:36:51,389 --> 01:36:53,829
I WENT OUT TO TAKE
THE LAUNDRY IN.

1480
01:36:55,360 --> 01:36:57,760
JUST LAID DOWN HERE.

1481
01:36:57,829 --> 01:36:59,629
I BEEN WATCHING THE STORM.

1482
01:37:03,034 --> 01:37:04,367
DO YOU THINK IT'S OVER?

1483
01:37:08,306 --> 01:37:11,251
YOU KNOW, YOUR BOY, HE WOULDN'T
SETTLE FOR A BOOK TONIGHT.

1484
01:37:11,275 --> 01:37:14,977
NO, HE WANTED A REAL STORY.

1485
01:37:15,046 --> 01:37:19,482
I TOLD HIM, "ALAN, YOU'RE GOING TO
HAVE TO TELL ME ONE. I'M JUST OUT.

1486
01:37:20,752 --> 01:37:22,084
"MY BRAIN'S..."

1487
01:37:24,456 --> 01:37:27,457
SO HE STARTS RIGHT
IN, "ONCE UPON A TIME..."

1488
01:37:29,994 --> 01:37:32,995
AND THE NEXT THING I
KNOW, HE'S SHAKING ME.

1489
01:37:33,064 --> 01:37:35,998
HE SAYS, "YOU CAN'T FALL
ASLEEP YET. IT'S NOT OVER."

1490
01:37:38,035 --> 01:37:39,435
I OPEN MY EYES.

1491
01:37:41,606 --> 01:37:44,206
THAT COWBOY LAMP.

1492
01:37:44,275 --> 01:37:48,511
THE SHADE'S RIPPED. I'M
STARING RIGHT AT THE LIGHT BULB.

1493
01:37:49,781 --> 01:37:51,280
AND IT BLEW.

1494
01:37:53,485 --> 01:37:57,052
USUALLY IT'S WHEN YOU
FLIP THE SWITCH, BUT...

1495
01:37:57,121 --> 01:38:00,456
I'D NEVER SEEN ONE
JUST GIVE OUT LIKE THAT.

1496
01:38:02,694 --> 01:38:05,495
JUST A TINY LITTLE POP.

1497
01:38:07,198 --> 01:38:10,199
I COULD FEEL IT RIGHT
DOWN MY SPINE, LEON.

1498
01:38:11,335 --> 01:38:13,269
INTO MY BONES.

1499
01:38:15,273 --> 01:38:17,573
IT'S LIKE THAT CARTOON
LIGHT BULB, YOU KNOW?

1500
01:38:17,642 --> 01:38:21,511
ABOVE YOUR HEAD,
ONLY THIS ONE WENT OFF.

1501
01:38:22,380 --> 01:38:24,414
NO IDEA.

1502
01:38:27,952 --> 01:38:30,420
NO IDEA I COULD BE THIS TIRED.

1503
01:38:33,458 --> 01:38:35,291
NO IDEA ABOUT ANYTHING.

1504
01:38:36,961 --> 01:38:41,531
I JUST SAT THERE, AND HE TOLD
THE REST OF THE STORY IN THE DARK.

1505
01:38:41,599 --> 01:38:43,933
SOMETHING ABOUT...

1506
01:38:44,001 --> 01:38:46,636
OH, GOD, HE WORKED
IT IN JUST THE WAY YOU...

1507
01:38:48,740 --> 01:38:51,607
THE ARMY SHOT OUT
THE SUN WITH A BAZOOKA

1508
01:38:51,676 --> 01:38:54,477
OR SOME DAMN THING LIKE THAT.

1509
01:38:57,782 --> 01:39:00,182
JUST GOT UP AND CAME OUT HERE.

1510
01:39:03,087 --> 01:39:04,821
IT MUST BE LATE.

1511
01:39:04,889 --> 01:39:06,489
[Thunder claps]

1512
01:39:15,500 --> 01:39:17,733
I'LL LET YOU GO TO BED.

1513
01:39:19,170 --> 01:39:20,610
[Marilyn] WHY...

1514
01:39:21,739 --> 01:39:23,272
WHY'D YOU COME HERE?

1515
01:39:29,714 --> 01:39:30,754
[Sighs]

1516
01:39:32,750 --> 01:39:33,883
SOME...

1517
01:39:33,952 --> 01:39:36,385
SOMETHING HAPPENED
TO ME, BUT, UH...

1518
01:39:39,190 --> 01:39:41,791
I FORGOT WHAT IT WAS.

1519
01:39:41,860 --> 01:39:43,459
[Thunder claps]

1520
01:39:48,165 --> 01:39:49,665
GOOD NIGHT.

1521
01:40:08,853 --> 01:40:12,822
[Tom Waits] <i>♪ I'LL PUT
FOOD ON THE TABLE ♪</i>

1522
01:40:12,891 --> 01:40:16,759
<i>♪ AND A ROOF OVERHEAD ♪</i>

1523
01:40:16,828 --> 01:40:20,062
<i>♪ BUT I'D TRADE IT
ALL TOMORROW ♪</i>

1524
01:40:20,999 --> 01:40:25,467
<i>♪ FOR THE HIGHWAY INSTEAD ♪</i>

1525
01:40:25,537 --> 01:40:30,006
<i>♪ WATCH YOU BACK,
THE ASH IS MADE ♪</i>

1526
01:40:30,074 --> 01:40:33,075
<i>♪ AND LOVE'S THE ONLY
THING I'VE EVER KNOWN ♪</i>

1527
01:40:34,211 --> 01:40:36,579
<i>♪ ONE THING'S FOR
SURE, PRETTY BABY ♪</i>

1528
01:40:36,648 --> 01:40:40,115
<i>♪ I ALWAYS TAKE
THE LONG WAY HOME ♪</i>

1529
01:40:55,867 --> 01:40:59,435
[Marilyn] <i>HIS NAME
WAS LEON, OR BARLOW,</i>

1530
01:40:59,503 --> 01:41:01,737
<i>OR ANY EPITHET THAT MIGHT APPLY.</i>

1531
01:41:07,278 --> 01:41:10,846
<i>LIKE A LOT OF WORDS, THE
NAME DIDN'T MEAN MUCH.</i>

1532
01:41:13,618 --> 01:41:16,719
<i>HE COULDN'T GET ANYONE
TO DO ANYTHING HE WANTED.</i>

1533
01:41:18,389 --> 01:41:20,556
<i>BUT AT LEAST HE
KNEW WHAT HE WANTED.</i>

1534
01:41:24,395 --> 01:41:28,631
<i>HE REMEMBERED WIND,
THE MUSIC IT MADE.</i>

1535
01:41:28,700 --> 01:41:31,834
<i>HE THOUGHT IT MUST SOUND
THE SAME IN HIS OWN LUNGS</i>

1536
01:41:31,903 --> 01:41:34,570
<i>RUSHING THROUGH THE
DARK CORRIDORS OF THE BODY.</i>

1537
01:41:38,109 --> 01:41:40,943
<i>HIS CURSE WAS REMEMBERING.</i>

1538
01:41:41,012 --> 01:41:43,012
<i>IT WAS ALSO A BLESSING.</i>

1539
01:41:45,416 --> 01:41:47,483
<i>THAT WAS EASY TO FORGET.</i>

1540
01:41:52,323 --> 01:41:54,101
<i>HE WAS SURE THAT
WHATEVER IT WAS,</i>

1541
01:41:54,125 --> 01:41:55,992
<i>BACK THERE IN THE DISTANCE,</i>

1542
01:41:56,060 --> 01:41:58,527
<i>IT COULD CHASE
ANYONE DOWN IN TIME.</i>

1543
01:42:18,349 --> 01:42:20,249
<i>NO ONE WOULD BE SPARED</i>

1544
01:42:20,317 --> 01:42:22,084
<i>AND FEW SPARED THE GRIEF</i>

1545
01:42:22,153 --> 01:42:24,453
<i>OF LOSING THOSE
WHO WOULD GO BEFORE.</i>

1546
01:42:35,232 --> 01:42:36,777
<i>THERE WAS NO BLAME, THEN,</i>

1547
01:42:36,801 --> 01:42:38,968
<i>TO LAY AT THE
FEET OF THE LIVING.</i>

1548
01:42:47,411 --> 01:42:49,723
POINT TO YOURSELF, YOU
GOT TO POINT TO YOURSELF,

1549
01:42:49,747 --> 01:42:51,992
SO HE KNOWS WHO
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

1550
01:42:52,016 --> 01:42:54,516
MONROE, WHY DO
YOU CALL HIM BOBBY?

1551
01:42:54,585 --> 01:42:56,385
WHY DOES HE CALL YOU BOBBY?

1552
01:42:58,589 --> 01:43:00,690
I DON'T KNOW, SON.

1553
01:43:07,531 --> 01:43:09,342
[Marilyn] <i>THERE WAS
ONLY THE OLD STRUGGLE</i>

1554
01:43:09,366 --> 01:43:11,067
<i>TO HOLD ON OR TO LET GO.</i>

1555
01:43:15,973 --> 01:43:18,273
<i>THERE WAS ONLY THE
STORY OF THE LOST FAMILY</i>

1556
01:43:18,342 --> 01:43:20,843
<i>RUNNING ALONG IN
THE NIGHT STREETS,</i>

1557
01:43:20,912 --> 01:43:22,544
<i>RUNNING FOR HOME.</i>

1558
01:43:24,515 --> 01:43:26,548
<i>WHATEVER THEY WERE RUNNING FROM,</i>

1559
01:43:26,617 --> 01:43:28,617
<i>HE KNEW HE HAD TO
SAVE THEM FROM IT</i>

1560
01:43:30,321 --> 01:43:32,621
<i>AND THAT HE WAS THE
ONLY ONE WHO COULD.</i>

1561
01:43:37,361 --> 01:43:38,761
[Train chugging]

1562
01:44:10,762 --> 01:44:11,961
<i>THEY WERE RUNNING.</i>

1563
01:44:12,429 --> 01:44:13,495
<i>RUNNING.</i>

1564
01:44:13,564 --> 01:44:14,564
<i>RUNNING.</i>

1565
01:44:15,800 --> 01:44:17,432
<i>THE WIND WAS BLOWING</i>

1566
01:44:17,501 --> 01:44:19,601
<i>AND HE COULD FEEL
THE COLD NIGHT AIR.</i>

1567
01:44:23,507 --> 01:44:25,207
<i>HE COULD SEE THE ROAD.</i>

1568
01:44:45,629 --> 01:44:49,464
<i>TO FIND OUT WHERE IT LED,
HE HAD ONLY TO GO THERE.</i>

1569
01:44:49,533 --> 01:44:52,501
<i>AND HE RAN AS FAST AS HE COULD,</i>

1570
01:44:53,637 --> 01:44:56,405
<i>NOT KNOWING HOW IT WOULD END,</i>

1571
01:44:59,877 --> 01:45:01,777
<i>KNOWING HE HAD TO KNOW.</i>

1572
01:45:51,979 --> 01:45:54,146
♪ [Tom Waits singing
<i>Long Way Home]</i>

1573
01:45:54,214 --> 01:45:56,198
<i>♪ MMM ♪</i>

1574
01:45:56,267 --> 01:45:58,033
<i>♪ MMM ♪</i>

1575
01:45:59,703 --> 01:46:01,703
<i>♪ MMM ♪</i>

1576
01:46:03,040 --> 01:46:05,307
<i>♪ MMM ♪</i>

1577
01:46:05,376 --> 01:46:08,177
<i>♪ YOU KNOW I LOVE YOU, BABY ♪</i>

1578
01:46:09,713 --> 01:46:12,948
<i>♪ MORE THAN THE
WHOLE WIDE WORLD ♪</i>

1579
01:46:13,984 --> 01:46:18,120
<i>♪ YOU'RE MY WOMAN ♪</i>

1580
01:46:18,189 --> 01:46:22,391
<i>♪ YOU KNOW YOU WERE MY PEARL ♪</i>

1581
01:46:22,460 --> 01:46:26,528
<i>♪ LET'S GO OUT PAST
THE PARTY LIGHTS ♪</i>

1582
01:46:26,597 --> 01:46:29,965
<i>♪ WHERE WE CAN
FINALLY BE ALONE ♪</i>

1583
01:46:31,135 --> 01:46:33,235
<i>♪ COME WITH ME ♪</i>

1584
01:46:33,304 --> 01:46:36,037
<i>♪ AND WE CAN TAKE
THE LONG WAY HOME ♪</i>

1585
01:46:36,107 --> 01:46:38,140
